post_cb({"5326546": {"ParentId": "5326491", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>Well, the standard states:</p>\n<p>3.6.1.3\n\"The function main shall not be used within a program.\"</p>\n<p>5.2.2.9\n\"Recursive calls are permitted, except to the function named main\"</p>\n<p>I guess it is beause main() is a special function used as the entry point to the program. I'd say keep it special, don't take it down the level of a normal function, because it is not.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "662630", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "5326546", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2011-03-16T14:14:00.630", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-16T14:14:00.630"}, "5326491": {"CommentCount": "6", "ViewCount": "3905", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2011-03-16T14:16:33.773", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "CreationDate": "2011-03-16T14:08:12.117", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-16T14:15:04.253", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T11:58:32.073", "FavoriteCount": "2", "Title": "Why are recursive main() calls not allowed in C++?", "Id": "5326491", "Score": "8", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5326491_5326491_0\"><strong>Possible Duplicates:</strong><br>\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4144030/restrictions-on-the-main-function\">restrictions on the main() function</a><br>\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4518598/is-it-legal-to-recurse-into-main-in-c\">Is it legal to recurse into main() in C++?</a> </br></br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I read in <em>C++ Primer</em> that <code>main</code> is not allowed to be called recursively, and in some related questions here on SO it is indeed confirmed that it is illegal.</p>\n<p>But why is it illegal? As long as you avoid a stack overflow, what's the problem with calling <code>main</code> within itself?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><main>", "OwnerUserId": "426092", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "5326547": {"ParentId": "5326491", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>I believe that the wording in 3.6.1/3 forbids this, saying it shall not be used in a program:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5326491_5326547_0\">The function main shall not be used\n  (3.2) within a program. The linkage\n  (3.5) of main is\n  implementation defined. A program that\n  declares main to be inline or static\n  is illformed. The name main is not\n  otherwise reserved. [Example: member\n  functions, classes, and enumerations\n  can be called main, as can entities in\n  other namespaces. ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then in 3.2/2</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5326491_5326547_1\">An object or nonoverloaded function is\n  used if its name appears in a\n  potentially evaluated expression.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This clearly indicates that used includes possible calls (which would be recursive) to <code>main</code>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "251738", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "5326547", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2011-03-16T14:14:07.453", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-16T14:14:07.453"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_5326491_5326547_1": {"section_id": 5811, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}, "so_5326491_5326547_0": {"section_id": 7147, "quality": 0.8064516129032258, "length": 25}}, "n3337": {"so_5326491_5326547_1": {"section_id": 5584, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}, "so_5326491_5326547_0": {"section_id": 6891, "quality": 0.8064516129032258, "length": 25}}, "n4659": {"so_5326491_5326547_1": {"section_id": 502, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}, "so_5326491_5326547_0": {"section_id": 8648, "quality": 0.7741935483870968, "length": 24}}}});